index 0000000..633e78d
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/matrix/monitoring.md
@@ -0,0 +1,68 @@
+# Matrix Monitoring And Alerts
+
+`runtime/matrix/observability.py` defines the process-local health contract for
+the Lydia Matrix adapter. It intentionally emits plain structured records so the
+existing Homelab health checks and fallback messenger can consume them without
+introducing another metrics stack.
+
+## Health Fields
+
+| Field | Meaning |
+|---|---|
+| `status` | `starting`, `healthy`, `degraded`, or `unhealthy` |
+| `adapter_healthy` | Whether the adapter can currently be treated as available |
+| `last_sync_at` | Unix timestamp of the last successful Matrix sync |
+| `sync_lag_seconds` | Age of the last successful sync |
+| `last_processed_event_id` | Most recent event handed to Lydia core |
+| `delivery_failures_total` | Monotonic outbound delivery-failure counter |
+| `quarantined_attachments_total` | Monotonic attachment-quarantine counter |
+| `generated_at` | Unix timestamp of the snapshot |
+
+Counters reset when the adapter process restarts. The operator monitor records
+deltas and restart events; Matrix remains a transport, not the authoritative
+store for task or monitoring state.
+
+## Thresholds
+
+| Signal | Warning | Critical | Operator action |
+|---|---:|---:|---|
+| Matrix sync lag | 60 seconds | 300 seconds | Check Synapse and adapter health; use Telegram or Signal fallback at critical |
+| Delivery failures | Any increase | Five consecutive failures | Verify Matrix reachability and credentials without logging their values |
+| Quarantined attachments | Any increase | Repeated rejection from one source | Review redacted reason and event ID; do not release binary data automatically |
+| Adapter health | n/a | Explicit unavailable state | Send fallback alert and retain external gateway operation |
+
+Disk use, PostgreSQL health, container state, TLS expiry, and backup age remain
+in the infrastructure health checks because the adapter cannot observe them
+reliably from inside its process.
+
+## Redaction Contract
+
+Audit and alert records contain event IDs, timestamps, counters, fixed reason
+codes, and exception class names only. They never contain message text,
+attachment bytes, access tokens, Authorization headers, homeserver responses,
+or exception strings. Unknown quarantine reasons fail closed instead of being
+copied into logs.
+
+## Fallback Alert
+
+`fallback_alert()` returns a payload for the existing Telegram or Signal
+gateway. The dispatcher selects an available external gateway at runtime; this
+module does not send messages itself.
+
+```json
+{
+  "type": "matrix.adapter.unhealthy",
+  "severity": "critical",
+  "reason": "sync_lag_critical",
+  "delivery_target": "external_gateway",
+  "metrics": {
+    "status": "unhealthy",
+    "adapter_healthy": false,
+    "sync_lag_seconds": 420
+  }
+}
+```
+
+The production alert should include the complete health snapshot but no message
+content. Recovery requires one successful sync and a new healthy snapshot; an
+alert does not authorize automatic restarts or deployment changes.
