+# Synapse ARM64 Proof of Concept — Plan
+
+## Purpose
+
+Validate that Synapse (with PostgreSQL) runs stably on the Raspberry Pi 5
+under the resource constraints of the existing Homelab, using immutable
+ARM64-capable container images, isolated networking, and HDD-backed storage.
+
+## Scope
+
+- Single-user idle and load behaviour.
+- Restart resilience (container crash, Docker daemon restart, host reboot).
+- Disk growth projection for database and media.
+- **Out of scope:** Federation, OIDC/Keycloak, frontproxy, external network
+  exposure, production configuration, multi-user performance.
+
+---
+
+## Image Digest Sources & Architecture Verification
+
+### Synapse
+
+| Property | Value |
+|----------|-------|
+| Registry | `ghcr.io` |
+| Repository | `element-hq/synapse` |
+| Pinned digest | `sha256:6882d26594b87171e0fe807ac6bd7f0000665cd70e73fb88c58ec9bff14c19ce` |
+| Media type | `application/vnd.oci.image.index.v1+json` (multi-arch OCI index) |
+| ARM64 manifest | `sha256:050587aeae69afdbb3f068747f420a32435135c6eb75c3dfec17d4e39b447fa9` |
+
+**Verification command:**
+```bash
+# Fetch the pinned OCI index digest (never mutable tags) and inspect platforms
+curl -s -H "Accept: application/vnd.oci.image.index.v1+json" \
+  -H "Authorization: Bearer $(curl -s 'https://ghcr.io/token?service=ghcr.io&scope=repository:element-hq/synapse:pull' | python3 -c 'import json,sys;print(json.load(sys.stdin).get("token",""))')" \
+  "https://ghcr.io/v2/element-hq/synapse/manifests/sha256:6882d26594b87171e0fe807ac6bd7f0000665cd70e73fb88c58ec9bff14c19ce" \
+  | python3 -c "
+import json,sys
+data=json.load(sys.stdin)
+for m in data.get('manifests',[]):
+    p=m.get('platform',{})
+    print(f\"{p.get('os','?')}/{p.get('architecture','?')} -> {m['digest']}\")
+"
+```
+
+Expected output includes: `linux/arm64 -> sha256:050587aeae69afdbb3f068747f420a32435135c6eb75c3dfec17d4e39b447fa9`
+
