+
+---
+
+## Versioned Configuration
+
+### File locations
+
+| File | Versioned path | Runtime mount target |
+|------|---------------|---------------------|
+| Compose file | `pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml` | — |
+| Synapse config | `pi/synapse-poc/homeserver.yaml` | `/data/homeserver.yaml` |
+| HDD data volume | — | `/mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/data` |
+| HDD media volume | — | `/mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/media` |
+| HDD db volume | — | `/mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/db` |
+
+### Bind-mount resolution
+
+The Compose file lives at `pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml`. The bind mount source
+`../synapse-poc/homeserver.yaml` resolves relative to the Compose directory to
+`pi/synapse-poc/homeserver.yaml`, i.e. the real versioned config file. The old
+wrong path `./synapse-poc/homeserver.yaml` (which would resolve to the
+nonexistent `pi/compose/synapse-poc/homeserver.yaml`) is rejected by static
+tests.
+
+### No `log_config` — stdout logging
+
+Synapse's `log_config` option defaults to `null` (see
+[documentation](https://element-hq.github.io/synapse/latest/usage/configuration/config_documentation.html#log_config)).
+When not set, Synapse uses its built-in Python logging configuration and writes
+logs to stdout/stderr. In a Docker container this is the expected behaviour —
+logs are visible via `docker logs synapse-poc`. No external log config file is
+needed. The versioned `pi/synapse-poc/homeserver.yaml` therefore omits
+`log_config` entirely.
+
+### Bootstrap — explicit key generation before Compose start
+
+The signing key and other required runtime material are generated by a
+dedicated bootstrap step **before** `docker compose up`. This follows the
+Synapse installation documentation's CLI contract for configuration generation
+(see [Synapse Installation Instructions](
+https://element-hq.github.io/synapse/latest/setup/installation.html#installing-as-a-python-module-from-pypi)):
+
+```bash
+docker run --rm \
+  -v /mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/data:/data \
+  --entrypoint python3 \
+  ghcr.io/element-hq/synapse@sha256:6882d26594b87171e0fe807ac6bd7f0000665cd70e73fb88c58ec9bff14c19ce \
+  -m synapse.app.homeserver \
+  --server-name synapse-poc.local \
+  --config-path /data/bootstrap.yaml \
+  --generate-config \
+  --report-stats=no
+```
+
+This command uses the exact Synapse image pinned in the Compose file, mounts the
+HDD data directory at `/data`, and runs the Synapse configuration generator
+inside the container. The `--rm` flag ensures the container is removed after
+generation. The `--entrypoint python3` override is required because the Synapse
+Docker image's default entrypoint is the Synapse server itself.
+
+The bootstrap command generates:
+- A signing key at `/data/synapse-poc.local.signing.key`
+- A temporary configuration file at `/data/bootstrap.yaml`
+- Other required runtime material (registration secret, etc.)
+
+After generation, the temporary bootstrap configuration is removed:
+
+```bash
+rm -f /mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/data/bootstrap.yaml
+```
+
+This preserves the signing key and other runtime material in the HDD data
+directory but neither overwrites nor modifies the readonly versioned
+`homeserver.yaml`. The bootstrap step is a one-time operation — on subsequent
+starts, the signing key already exists and Synapse uses it directly.
+
+### No committed secrets
+
+The versioned config contains no secrets, keys, tokens, or passwords.
+Database credentials are non-secret PoC defaults (`synapse_poc`). The signing
+key is generated by the bootstrap step in the HDD data path. Registration is
+disabled (`enable_registration: false`).
+
+### Config path assertions (static tests)
+
+Static tests validate:
+1. All config path references point to existing versioned files.
+2. The bind-mount source resolves to `pi/synapse-poc/homeserver.yaml`.
+3. The old wrong path `pi/compose/synapse-poc/homeserver.yaml` is rejected.
+4. `signing_key_path` is set and points under `/data`.
+5. No `log_config` is set (stdout logging by default).
+6. The plan documents the exact bootstrap command with `--generate-config`,
+   `--config-path /data/bootstrap.yaml`, `--server-name synapse-poc.local`,
+   `--report-stats=no`, the pinned image digest, and the cleanup of
+   `bootstrap.yaml`.
+7. The procedure order is: HDD directories → Bootstrap → Compose start →
+   Health → Measurements.
+
+---
+
+## Pass / Fail Budgets
+
+### G1 — Idle (steady state, no active sync)
+
+| Metric | Expected | Budget (pass) | Measurement command |
+|--------|----------|---------------|---------------------|
+| RAM (Synapse + PostgreSQL) | ≤ 1 024 MB | ≤ 1 280 MB | `docker stats --no-stream synapse-poc synapse-poc-db --format '{{.Name}} {{.MemUsage}}'` |
+| CPU (containers, idle) | ≤ 5 % (1 core) | ≤ 10 % | `docker stats --no-stream synapse-poc synapse-poc-db --format '{{.Name}} {{.CPUPerc}}'` |
+
+### G2 — Load (active sync, 100 messages / min for 5 min)
+
+| Metric | Expected | Budget (pass) | Measurement command |
+|--------|----------|---------------|---------------------|
+| RAM during load | ≤ 1 280 MB | ≤ 1 536 MB | `docker stats --no-stream synapse-poc --format '{{.MemUsage}}'` |
+| CPU during load | ≤ 30 % (1 core) | ≤ 50 % | `docker stats --no-stream synapse-poc --format '{{.CPUPerc}}'` |
+
+Load generation (inside the synapse container — no published host ports):
+```bash
+# Send 100 messages per minute for 5 minutes via Synapse client API.
+# Executed inside the synapse container via docker exec (no host port needed).
+# (Requires an access token — use register_new_matrix_user or admin API)
+docker exec synapse-poc sh -c '
+  for i in $(seq 1 5); do
+    for j in $(seq 1 100); do
+      curl -s -X POST -d "{\"msgtype\":\"m.text\",\"body\":\"load test $i-$j\"}" \
+        "http://localhost:8008/_matrix/client/v3/rooms/!<room_id>:synapse-poc.local/send/m.room.message" \
+        -H "Authorization: Bearer <access_token>" > /dev/null
+    done
+    sleep 60
+  done
+'
+```
+
+### G3 — Restart
+
+| Scenario | Expected | Budget | Measurement command |
+|----------|----------|--------|---------------------|
+| Container restart (synapse) | Healthy within 60 s | ≤ 90 s | `docker restart synapse-poc && time docker exec synapse-poc python3 -c "import urllib.request; urllib.request.urlopen('http://localhost:8008/health', timeout=90)"` |
+| Full stack restart | Both healthy within 120 s | ≤ 180 s | `docker compose -f pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml down && docker compose -f pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml up -d && sleep 180 && docker compose -f pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml ps --health` |
+
+### G4 — Disk
+
+| Metric | Expected | Budget (pass) | Measurement command |
+|--------|----------|---------------|---------------------|
+| DB size (idle, initial) | < 10 MB | < 20 MB | `docker exec synapse-poc-db psql -U synapse -d synapse -c "SELECT pg_database_size('synapse')/1024/1024 AS size_mb;"` |
+| Media size (idle, initial) | < 1 MB | < 5 MB | `du -sh /mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/media 2>/dev/null || echo "media dir not yet created"` |
+| DB growth (30d / 100 msg/d) | ≤ 50 MB | ≤ 100 MB | *Long-running — evaluate after 30 days* |
+
+---
+
+## Operator Blackbox Procedure
+
+The operator follows these steps on the **Pi 5** (`192.168.2.30`).
+No manual config editing is needed — the versioned files are complete.
+
+### Step 1 — Create HDD directories
+
+```bash
+# Ensure HDD-backed directories for PoC data (all three HDD volumes defined in compose)
+sudo mkdir -p /mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/{data,media,db}
+```
+
+The Compose file (`pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml`) already defines the HDD-backed
+`driver_opts` for all three volumes with correct device paths. No manual Compose
+edit is needed.
+
+### Step 2 — Bootstrap runtime material
+
+Generate the signing key and other required runtime material **before** the
+first Compose start. This uses the exact Synapse image pinned in the Compose
+file, following the Synapse installation documentation's CLI contract:
+
+```bash
+docker run --rm \
+  -v /mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/data:/data \
+  --entrypoint python3 \
+  ghcr.io/element-hq/synapse@sha256:6882d26594b87171e0fe807ac6bd7f0000665cd70e73fb88c58ec9bff14c19ce \
+  -m synapse.app.homeserver \
+  --server-name synapse-poc.local \
+  --config-path /data/bootstrap.yaml \
+  --generate-config \
+  --report-stats=no
+```
+
+After generation, remove the temporary bootstrap configuration (the signing key
+and other runtime material persist in the HDD data directory):
+
+```bash
+rm -f /mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/data/bootstrap.yaml
+```
+
+The versioned `homeserver.yaml` sets:
+
+```yaml
+signing_key_path: /data/synapse-poc.local.signing.key
+```
+
+The signing key is now present in the HDD data directory before the first
+Compose start. The readonly versioned `homeserver.yaml` is never overwritten.
+
+Signing key location after bootstrap:
+```
+/mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/data/synapse-poc.local.signing.key
+```
+
+### Step 3 — Start the stack
+
+```bash
+docker compose -f pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml up -d
+```
+
+Wait until the containers transition to `healthy` (monitor with
+`watch docker compose -f pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml ps`).
+
+### Step 4 — Run health checks
+
+```bash
+# Check both containers are healthy
+docker compose -f pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml ps
+
+# Test Synapse health endpoint (inside container — no published ports)
+docker exec synapse-poc python3 -c \
+  "import urllib.request; print(urllib.request.urlopen('http://localhost:8008/health', timeout=10).read())"
+
+# Test PostgreSQL connection
+docker exec synapse-poc-db pg_isready -U synapse -d synapse
+
+# Verify signing key was created by bootstrap step
+ls -la /mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc/data/synapse-poc.local.signing.key
+```
+
+### Step 5 — Measure idle metrics (G1)
+
+Run the G1 measurement commands from the budgets table above.
+
+### Step 6 — Run load test (G2)
+
+Execute the load generation script from G2 inside the synapse container
+while monitoring with `docker stats`. No published host ports are required.
+
+### Step 7 — Test restart resilience (G3)
+
+Execute the G3 restart scenarios from the budgets table above.
+
+### Step 8 — Measure disk usage (G4)
+
+Execute the G4 measurement commands from the budgets table above.
+
+### Step 9 — Tear down
+
+```bash
+docker compose -f pi/compose/synapse-poc.yml down -v
+# Optionally remove HDD-backed data
+# sudo rm -rf /mnt/hardDrive/docker/synapse-poc
+```
+
+---
+
+## Pass / Fail Decision
+
+All G1–G4 budgets must be within the **pass** column for the PoC to be
+considered successful. If any metric exceeds the budget, the PoC fails and
+the issue must be documented before retry.
+
+| Gate | Result (pass/fail) | Notes |
+|------|-------------------|-------|
+| G1 — Idle | | |
+| G2 — Load | | |
+| G3 — Restart | | |
+| G4 — Disk | | |
+
+**Overall:** _pass / fail_ (circle one)
+
+Signed-off by operator: \_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_ Date: \_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_
