+# Matrix Reverse Proxy and TLS Contract
+
+`matrix.hl.maier.wtf` is served exclusively through the existing frontproxy and
+ACME companion. Synapse listens on plain HTTP port 8008 inside Docker; the
+frontproxy terminates public HTTPS and forwards requests over
+`frontproxy_default`.
+
+## Runtime Contract
+
+- Only Synapse joins `frontproxy_default`; PostgreSQL remains on the internal
+  database network.
+- Synapse declares `VIRTUAL_HOST` and `LETSENCRYPT_HOST` as
+  `matrix.hl.maier.wtf`, `VIRTUAL_PORT` as `8008`, and the established ACME
+  contact `webmaster@maier.wtf`.
+- Synapse exposes port 8008 to Docker networks but publishes no host port.
+- The Synapse listener has TLS disabled because TLS terminates at frontproxy.
+  It trusts forwarded headers and advertises
+  `https://matrix.hl.maier.wtf/` as its public base URL.
+
+DNS creation, certificate requests, Compose deployment, and proxy changes are
+separate operator-authorized actions and are not performed by this contract.
+
+## Operator Smoke Test
+
+Run these checks only after the stack and DNS have been deployed through the
+approved operational workflow.
+
+1. Confirm that Synapse has no published host port:
+
+   ```bash
+   container_id="$(docker compose ps -q synapse)"
+   test -n "$container_id"
+   test "$(docker inspect --format '{{json .HostConfig.PortBindings}}' "$container_id")" = "null"
+   ```
+
+   Expected: all commands exit with status 0 and Docker reports no host port
+   bindings.
+
+2. Check the public Matrix client endpoint through HTTPS:
+
+   ```bash
+   curl --fail --silent --show-error \
+     https://matrix.hl.maier.wtf/_matrix/client/versions
+   ```
+
+   Expected: HTTP 200 with a JSON `versions` response.
+
+3. Verify the certificate chain and hostname:
+
+   ```bash
+   openssl s_client -connect matrix.hl.maier.wtf:443 -servername matrix.hl.maier.wtf \
+     -verify_hostname matrix.hl.maier.wtf -verify_return_error </dev/null
+   ```
+
+   Expected: the certificate is valid for `matrix.hl.maier.wtf` and OpenSSL
+   reports `Verify return code: 0 (ok)`.
